                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d574">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">493.11 <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_EH1"
                        >Ekvall, Henry</persName>/30: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JNT1"
                            type="from">Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-10-06T14:00:00+08:00"
                            >October 6, 1932—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received October 6—5:10 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1170. Legation’s 1153, October 1, noon. I have instructed
                        <persName>Peck</persName> as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“October 6, 3 p.m. Your September 30, 3 p.m. Please ascertain when
                            special emissary of General <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_CK4"
                                >Chiang</persName> will proceed to Sian to investigate <persName
                                corresp="frus1932v03#p_EH1">Ekvall</persName> case. Inform Foreign
                            Office that Legation desires to send its representative to Sian to give
                            assistance in such further investigation and request that appropriate
                            instructions be issued by General <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_CK4"
                                >Chiang</persName> for his representative to cooperate with the
                            representative of this Legation.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JNT1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
